OL,3,CFarmer says relentless wet weather has
OL,4,Cleft his crops 'rotting in the ground'
OL,6,F"We'll continue to listen to farmers
OL,7,Fand look at how we can expand the
OL,8,Fscheme and improve support for those
OL,9,Faffected."
OL,11,FClimate change expert Professor Nicola
OL,12,FCannon from Royal Agricultural
OL,13,FUniversity in Cirencester said: "Crops
OL,14,Fhave got relatively poor root systems
OL,15,Fbecause they have sat in wet soil all
OL,16,Fwinder so they haven't had to scavenge
OL,17,Ffor water, so if it turns dry they are
OL,18,Flikely to become moisture stressed
OL,19,Fvery quickly."
